cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of learning a low-dimensional geometric structure underlying distributed data, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a distributed algorithm that involves communication between different sites, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper includes numerical experiments on real and synthetic data, which could make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
